title: Android uses the legacy Hebrew language code of `iw`.  Added a symlink for
message:
Android uses the legacy Hebrew language code of `iw`.  Added a symlink for
devices that use the modern `he` code.

Ref: https://android.googlesource.com/platform/packages/apps/Settings/+/master/res/

`values-iw` exists, but `values-he` does not.

This exposed a bunch of layout issues in RTL which I'm not really happy
with, but I'm not yet sure if there's an issue with my Android setup which
is causing it.

title: Correct is{First,Last}InSection to use .getDate instead of .getDay. (Fixes #15)
message:
Correct is{First,Last}InSection to use .getDate instead of .getDay. (Fixes #15)

The error would cause the date header in the trip history to not be shown if
two trips were in the same year and month but the same day of the week.  For
example, two trips on 2016-03-16 and 2016-03-23 would only ever show one of
the headers, because they are on the same day of the week (Wednesday) in the
same month and year.

title: Merge "Trips" and "Refills" into "History", acknowledge nfc-felica-lib
message:
Merge "Trips" and "Refills" into "History", acknowledge nfc-felica-lib

* Merge "Trips" and "Refills" into "History", like what the Japanese cards
  did.

* Removed Trip.getFare, replaced with Trip.hasFare, as this was only ever
  used in the context of determining if a fare should be charged for a
  journey.

* Added a patch to convert Refills into Trips, until such time individual
  implementations have been fixed up to do this better.

* Acknowledged nfc-felica-lib in Licenses activity.

title: Fix reading Singapore NETS Flashpay from credit cards (codebutler/farebot#114)
message:
Fix reading Singapore NETS Flashpay from credit cards (codebutler/farebot#114)

In Singapore, there are many credit cards which contain Nets Flashpay
application.  However Farebot cannot read them correctly.  This will select
the correct application before attempting to read the card, in order to be
compatible with these credit cards.

title: Read full transaction history from CEPAS cards
message:
Read full transaction history from CEPAS cards

Read purse Lc=01 for transaction log with start offset of 0x00 only
returns last 15 transactions. Added a second read starting with offset
0x0F to read the rest, combining the results.
Also modified wrapMessage to not set parameters.length after Lc since it's not
in the spec.

Read purse transaction log with number of bytes to read

Reading purse transaction log with starting offset but not passing number of bytes to read sometimes result in 6700 response.
Added number of bytes to read based on number of records contained in purse detail.
